command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateAutomationNodeType

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateAutomationNodeTypeParameter
command.description: Updates an automation parameter of an Automation Node Type.

command.description: Deletes an automation parameter of a Automation Node Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateAutomationNodeType
command.description: Updates an Automation Node Type entity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Creates an Automation Node Instance entity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Updates an Automation Node Instance entity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Deletes an Automation Node Instance.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteAutomationNodeType
command.description: Deletes an Automation Node Type.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ApproveAutomationNodeType
command.description: Sets the status of the Automation Node Type to Approved so that the Automation Node Type can be activated to the Automation Gateway Server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ApproveAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Sets the status of the Automation Node Instance to Approved so that the Automation Node Instance can be activated to the Automation Gateway Server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateAutomationNodeInstanceParameter
command.description: Updates an automation parameter of an Automation Node Instance.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.Activate
command.description: Fires an event to activate the Automation Gateway configuration to the Automation Gateways server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.CreateAutomationChannel
command.description: Creates an Automation Channel entity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UpdateAutomationChannel
command.description: Updates an Automation Channel entity.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteAutomationChannel
command.description: Deletes an Automation Channel.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ApproveAutomationChannel
command.description: Sets the status of the Automation Channel to Approved so that the Automation Channel can be activated to the Automation Gateway Server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.AlignActivatedEntities
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Aligns the status of the entities activated on the Automation layer.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeAutomationNodeType
command.description: Configures the Automation Node Type to be read-only by setting the attribute IsLocked to True.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UnfreezeAutomationNodeType
command.description: Removes the read-only setting from the Automation Node Type by setting the attribute IsLocked to False.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.FreezeAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Configures the Automation Node Instance to be read-only by setting the attribute IsLocked to True.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.UnfreezeAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Removes the read-only setting from the Automation Node Instance by setting the attribute IsLocked to False.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ActivateAutomationChannel
command.description: Fires an event to activate the Automation Gateway Channel configuration to the Automation Gateways Server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.AlignActivatedAutomationChannels
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Aligns the status of the Automation Channels activated on the Automation layer.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ExportAutomationConfig
command.description: Exports the current Automation Configuration in CSV format.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ImportAutomationConfig
command.description: Imports an Automation Configuration in CSV format.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ResetEnvironment
command.description: Clears the configuration on the Automation Gateway Server.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.Deactivate
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Reverts all the entities in the Automation Gateway which are in Pending status to their previous Approved or Dismissed status.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.DeleteHistory
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Deletes the records of the Activation History.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.AlignEntitiesToBeReset
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Aligns the status of the entities on the automation layer for the reset operation.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.RevertAutomationNodeType
command.description: Reverts the selected Automation Node Type and its instances to the activated version.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.RevertAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Reverts the selected Automation Node Instance to the activated version.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.CopyAutomationNodeInstance
command.description: Makes a copy of the given Automation Node Instance.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.MigrateAutomation
command.description: Migrates the automation entities from the previous version to the current version.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ManageFailureOfImportWithReset
command.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. Manage the failure of the Import With Reset command.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ApproveAllAutomationNodeTypes
command.description: Approves all Automation Node Types and related Instances which are in **To Be Approved** status.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.ApproveAllAutomationNodeInstances
command.description: Approves all Automation Node Instances which are in **To Be Approved** status.

command.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Commands.IsMigrationNecessary
command.description: True if the data of Automation Gateway need to be migrated, false otherwise.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.AutomationReadyForCPM
event.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. This event is fired to activate all the approved entities to the Automation Gateway Server.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.AutomationUpdatedOnCPM
event.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. This event is fired when all the entities have been activated to Automation Gateway Server.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.AutomationActivated
event.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. This event is fired when the Operational domain has been aligned with the Automation Gateway Server.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.ActivateFinished
event.description: This event is fired once the Activate procedure has updated the status on ATN_MS for all the entities activated to the Automation Gateway Server. This event is associated to the signal ActivateFinishedSignal.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.ResetEnvironmentDone
event.description: FOR INTERNAL USE ONLY. This event is fired when the reset of the configuration on the Automation Gateway Server has finished.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.ResetFinished
event.description: This event is fired when the reset of the configuration on the Automation Gate Server has finished. This event is associated to the signal ResetFinishedSignal.

event.name: Siemens.SimaticIT.MasterData.ATN_MS.MSModel.Events.ImportFinished
event.description: This event is fired once the Import procedure has completed. This event is associated to the signal ImportFinishedSignal.
